1
00:00:01,751 --> 00:00:03,795
<i>Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.</i>

2
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:07,132
<i>People who have used these drugs</i>

3
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:10,760
<i>are now estimated</i>
<i>to total two million in Japan.</i>

4
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:14,347
<i>The number of people arrested</i>
<i>for drug-related offenses</i>

5
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:17,142
<i>is as many as 14,000 yearly.</i>

6
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:20,020
If you come any closer,

7
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:22,355
I'll jump off!

8
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:24,858
You're going to jump? Then get on with it.

9
00:00:24,941 --> 00:00:25,775
No way.

10
00:00:30,572 --> 00:00:31,823
Mad Dog.

11
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:34,951
<i>You're an S for the police</i>
<i>while being an S for the NCD.</i>

12
00:00:35,035 --> 00:00:37,954
Kurosaki or me?

13
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:39,664
Think hard.

14
00:00:39,748 --> 00:00:42,208
-I didn't do anything!
-Screw you!

15
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,377
<i>Even if it was against their will,</i>

16
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:48,173
<i>once consumed, one's body</i>
<i>will never forget the taste of drugs.</i>

17
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:50,425
<i>They get addicted</i>
<i>without even realizing it.</i>

18
00:00:50,508 --> 00:00:52,510
<i>I don't know jack about cocaine.</i>

19
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:54,929
Like hell I'm giving you my urine!

20
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:59,225
You refuse to offer your urine
for testing, correct?

21
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:00,935
Stay still, okay?

22
00:01:01,019 --> 00:01:02,854
You'll injure your urethra!

23
00:01:02,937 --> 00:01:04,105
No!

24
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:06,149
The reason you're still here

25
00:01:06,232 --> 00:01:09,402
is because your father
is a senior commissioner and my superior.

26
00:01:09,986 --> 00:01:13,281
-I'm aware.
-Then bring me results, not words.

27
00:01:13,364 --> 00:01:15,033
Never lose to the NCD again.

28
00:01:15,116 --> 00:01:15,992
Yes, sir.

29
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:19,788
What do you want?

30
00:01:25,084 --> 00:01:26,169
Wait, what?

31
00:01:43,436 --> 00:01:46,439
Your next mission is to mislead the NCD

32
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:49,484
and leak information
on the cocaine supplier to me.

33
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:52,529
How? Kurosaki is at the hospital, right?

34
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:58,076
The NCD will be desperate to make Kaga
spill the source of his cocaine.

35
00:01:58,576 --> 00:02:00,954
But Kaga won't talk so easily.

36
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:02,372
I bet.

37
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:05,583
If he talks,
he's in for an even worse time than now.

38
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,877
Their world isn't so simple.

39
00:02:09,254 --> 00:02:13,258
It's a lot like how you had to quit acting
after you got violent while drunk.

40
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:14,259
Buzz off.

41
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:19,347
Once Kaga gets out of prison,
he won't be able to appear on TV anymore.

42
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:22,225
But at his age,
it will be hard to find other work.

43
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:24,060
In order for him to survive,

44
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:27,981
he'll need patrons
who help get him business.

45
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:31,943
If he gives up his patrons
who supply him with cocaine

46
00:02:32,026 --> 00:02:35,280
and have criminal connections,
he won't live long.

47
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:38,908
That is why Kaga will stay silent.

48
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:43,371
This way, his patrons will help him
get more work, however small, later on.

49
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:47,917
One scumbag backed by other scumbags, huh?

50
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:49,711
Finding and arresting suppliers

51
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:52,964
is the biggest accomplishment
for an investigative team.

52
00:02:53,047 --> 00:02:56,926
We can crush the entire operation
by following the trail from there.

53
00:02:57,719 --> 00:03:02,223
It's a much greater success
than arresting a random punk dealer.

54
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:05,184
That accomplishment must fall
into the police's hands.

55
00:03:06,269 --> 00:03:08,771
But Kaga won't talk, right?

56
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:11,858
Will the NCD get any info for me to leak?

57
00:03:12,650 --> 00:03:14,235
What's there for me to do?

58
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:18,573
The NCD has Kurosaki, who'll use
any means to make a suspect talk.

59
00:03:18,656 --> 00:03:21,784
You just stay close to Kurosaki
and feed his info to me.

60
00:03:22,327 --> 00:03:24,370
Do that, and Kurosaki and the NCD,

61
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:26,956
the police's rivals,
will lose their reputation.

62
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:31,127
On the other hand, my standing
within the police will skyrocket.

63
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:35,506
I thought the police
were supposed to uphold justice.

64
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:38,843
Yet all you want is status
and accomplishments to your name.

65
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:43,223
I'm sure it's tough to understand
for someone who threw away half his life.

66
00:03:43,306 --> 00:03:44,182
Geez.

67
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:47,894
Both you and Kurosaki are so bizarre.

68
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:49,520
Don't lump me in with him.

69
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:54,067
That guy is just
a revenge-obsessed wraith.

70
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:56,194
What does that mean?

71
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:01,532
Wait.

72
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,619
You're his S without
knowing anything about him?

73
00:04:05,161 --> 00:04:06,204
Kind of.

74
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,670
Look, you're going to die
if you genuinely stick with him.

75
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:19,634
The NCD was investigating
a case back then,

76
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:22,053
but it ended up going to the police.

77
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:26,975
His mother
wasn't just a regular meth addict.

78
00:04:28,184 --> 00:04:30,937
She had been cheating
with a yakuza guy for years.

79
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:33,022
She was fed meth and forced

80
00:04:34,524 --> 00:04:36,317
into becoming a sex addict.

81
00:04:37,735 --> 00:04:38,736
Chemsex?

82
00:04:40,029 --> 00:04:42,031
A lot worse than that.

83
00:05:45,261 --> 00:05:46,554
What's that?

84
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:50,600
Something that will feel even better.

85
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:58,733
<i>Kurosaki was part of an ordinary household</i>
<i>which fell into ruin because of meth.</i>

86
00:05:59,942 --> 00:06:01,944
<i>His mother gradually got addicted,</i>

87
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:04,906
<i>dug into their savings,</i>
<i>and once the money ran out,</i>

88
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:07,408
<i>the yakuza forced her into prostitution.</i>

89
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:15,166
<i>The yakuza make money by feeding drugs</i>
<i>to housewives with that goal in mind.</i>

90
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:18,586
<i>Any money earned from prostitution</i>
<i>just goes back to drugs.</i>

91
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:22,131
<i>A never-ending cycle of misery,</i>
<i>just like the yakuza want.</i>

92
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:31,099
<i>However, humans really struggle</i>
<i>with accepting who they become</i>

93
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:33,142
<i>when they're at their lowest.</i>

94
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:35,144
<i>His mother,</i>

95
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:38,106
who bought meth by selling her body,

96
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:41,317
had convinced herself
that she was loved by the man.

97
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:43,027
What?

98
00:06:44,153 --> 00:06:45,196
And then,

99
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:48,407
things only got worse.

100
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:01,295
Hey, stop it!

101
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:03,047
Let me go!

102
00:07:19,313 --> 00:07:22,024
<i>It took less than a year</i>
<i>for his mother to break.</i>

103
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:24,819
-How dare you steal my lover?
<i>-Then that day came.</i>

104
00:07:24,902 --> 00:07:27,071
<i>His mother caused an incident.</i>

105
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:32,577
-You're such a pain, you damn bitch!
-Who is this hag?

106
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:34,912
You're being fooled by that woman!

107
00:07:35,746 --> 00:07:39,083
You love me, don't you?

108
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:41,252
She's my woman.

109
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:44,672
You're just a way to make some cash.

110
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:47,258
Gross hag.

111
00:07:48,342 --> 00:07:49,635
-Let's go.
-Yeah.

112
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:51,304
She's so gross.

113
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:52,805
Give me a break.

114
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:08,905
It's your fault.

115
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:12,325
It's your fault.

116
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:16,996
Die.

117
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:18,331
Die!

118
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:20,166
Die!

119
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:21,918
Die!

120
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:22,919
Die!

121
00:08:23,961 --> 00:08:26,130
Die!

122
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:31,177
Drug-induced psychosis?

123
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:35,431
Afterwards, when the police went
to their residence searching for her,

124
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:39,936
<i>Kurosaki, still a middle schooler,</i>
<i>was standing there blankly,</i>

125
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:44,815
<i>with his mother's corpse</i>
<i>hanging by a noose in front of him.</i>

126
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:46,567
Half a year later,

127
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:50,571
his father, overcome with despair,
drowned himself in the sea.

128
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,116
Meth laid waste to his family.

129
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:58,496
That's why he bears
a deep hatred for drugs.

130
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:01,123
To avenge his mother.

131
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:05,586
Oh, hey, eat it before it burns.

132
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:09,549
Is that why he…

133
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:12,093
Why!

134
00:09:13,594 --> 00:09:15,763
Why the hell?

135
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:18,766
It's just a drug addict who died.

136
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:21,227
Ouch!

137
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:23,479
Try saying that again.

138
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:24,981
What?

139
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:26,857
I'll kill you.

140
00:09:30,778 --> 00:09:33,614
So he's not just an asshole.

141
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:38,786
I'll die before I let you off the hook.

142
00:09:39,537 --> 00:09:44,417
You're going to tell me in great detail
where you've been getting your cocaine.

143
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:47,628
How many times do I have to tell you?

144
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:49,839
I don't know anything!

145
00:09:50,339 --> 00:09:52,425
Nothing! Zilch--

146
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:57,847
Once the urine test comes back,
it will be confirmed that you did cocaine.

147
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:00,641
So what?

148
00:10:01,183 --> 00:10:05,563
Even if that happens, my only crimes
are possession and use of cocaine.

149
00:10:05,646 --> 00:10:09,525
Big deal. It's my first offense,
so I'll just get a suspended sentence.

150
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:12,945
I won't let that happen.

151
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:16,324
What, you're going to use violence now?

152
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:19,160
I'll sue you if you get violent!

153
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:23,456
What? Who's going
to get violent with whom now?

154
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:32,423
You…

155
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:34,717
What are you doing?

156
00:10:36,177 --> 00:10:38,262
That establishes assault.

157
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:41,015
Possession and use
may get you a suspended sentence,

158
00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:44,268
but you're definitely going to prison
with assault added on top.

159
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:46,562
Wait! Don't hit me anymore, Kaga!

160
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:48,731
Stop! Please stop!

161
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:57,114
Assault? When you're the one
hitting yourself?

162
00:10:57,198 --> 00:10:59,617
Like hell that will pass!

163
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:02,745
I'm hitting myself? No.

164
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:05,122
You're the one hitting me.

165
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:09,085
You're going to frame me by doing that?

166
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:12,963
Would the NCD do something that unjust?

167
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:14,632
Unjust, you say?

168
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:19,011
After you unjustly hurt all those women?

169
00:11:20,888 --> 00:11:22,723
Now then, what will you do?

170
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:25,559
Keep feigning ignorance and go to prison?

171
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:29,480
Or will you fess up and stay free
with just a suspended sentence?

172
00:11:29,563 --> 00:11:30,398
Choose.

173
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:33,401
I fucking told you, I don't know anything!

174
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:35,027
Get me my lawyer!

175
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,204
The hell are you doing?

176
00:11:56,757 --> 00:11:59,844
And there are the fingerprints.

177
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:07,852
This adds damage to property
on top of inflicting bodily injury.

178
00:12:09,103 --> 00:12:13,858
Even with a good lawyer, you'll get
over a year in prison for certain.

179
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:17,611
Your prison life keeps
getting longer and longer.

180
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:19,530
Anything goes, huh?

181
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:24,577
Come on, man!

182
00:12:24,660 --> 00:12:27,538
Cutting my face? Have you gone insane?

183
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:30,875
Are you fucking mad?

184
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,380
Don't make me repeat myself.

185
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,507
I have my own methods.

186
00:12:39,049 --> 00:12:40,301
Listen up.

187
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:42,052
Even if you don't talk,

188
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:44,722
we'll conduct searches
at random criminal hideouts.

189
00:12:44,805 --> 00:12:46,223
At each one,

190
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:49,435
we'll declare that Kaga
gave up his supplier.

191
00:12:49,518 --> 00:12:51,353
What do you think will happen?

192
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:54,148
Even if you get out of prison,

193
00:12:54,231 --> 00:12:57,526
do you think the criminals
will just leave you be?

194
00:12:58,819 --> 00:13:02,198
Is it worth going to such lengths
to protect your supplier?

195
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:05,451
If they'll treat you
as a traitor either way,

196
00:13:05,534 --> 00:13:10,706
wouldn't it be better to at least
get the suspended sentence?

197
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:54,959
KYONOSUKE UMEZAWA

198
00:14:46,635 --> 00:14:48,012
What?

199
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:50,472
You're terrifying.

200
00:14:50,556 --> 00:14:52,975
Kaga gave up his cocaine supplier.

201
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:54,894
And you just start talking?

202
00:14:54,977 --> 00:14:58,063
His supplier is a guy named Nagata.

203
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:01,650
He's a patron and a partner
in his nightly activities.

204
00:15:01,734 --> 00:15:05,321
To cover his tracks,
Kaga didn't buy directly from a dealer,

205
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:07,990
he bought it through Nagata instead.

206
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:10,618
Nagata is the CEO of a food company.

207
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:13,996
The NCD has marked him as our next target.

208
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:17,625
Isn't that classified information?

209
00:15:18,125 --> 00:15:19,668
Should you be telling me?

210
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:23,589
You fulfilled your role as an S last time.

211
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:26,634
That's why I've decided to trust you.

212
00:15:27,968 --> 00:15:30,012
I have your trust all of a sudden?

213
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:31,305
Kind of gross.

214
00:15:31,388 --> 00:15:34,308
This case doesn't end
with just arresting Kaga.

215
00:15:34,391 --> 00:15:38,687
It only ends when we uncover
and destroy the source of the drugs.

216
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,607
That's why I want your cooperation again.

217
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:44,234
What do I have to do?

218
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:46,070
Back at HQ,

219
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:50,616
they're looking into the suspect first
before they decide on a course of action.

220
00:15:50,699 --> 00:15:53,786
So no specific instructions
until they finish that?

221
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:56,830
That will be too slow.
We're fighting against time.

222
00:15:57,498 --> 00:16:02,628
You'll go sell tons of drugs
to crooks connected to Kaga.

223
00:16:02,711 --> 00:16:05,047
What? To first-time customers?

224
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:08,133
They'll be super suspicious
if I sell a large amount!

225
00:16:08,217 --> 00:16:09,301
I bet they will.

226
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:10,928
-Then why?
-Because…

227
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:14,848
If you sell the drugs at a lower price
compared to the market rate,

228
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:17,851
the crooks will say this to their dealers,

229
00:16:17,935 --> 00:16:21,355
"I know a cheaper way to buy the drugs."

230
00:16:21,897 --> 00:16:23,315
What will happen then?

231
00:16:23,899 --> 00:16:25,401
If I did that,

232
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:29,780
the traffickers would come and kill me
so they can protect their own profits.

233
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:32,658
-Which is where we'll arrest them!
-Hang on a second!

234
00:16:32,741 --> 00:16:34,785
-What?
-Don't give me that.

235
00:16:34,868 --> 00:16:37,579
They'll go after my life.
I could get killed!

236
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:39,957
It's fine. We'll catch them before that.

237
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:42,960
What if I die?

238
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:46,296
Don't.

239
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:47,881
Don't make it sound simple!

240
00:16:48,465 --> 00:16:50,342
That's too dangerous for me.

241
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:53,262
I told you I decided to trust you.

242
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:54,847
Yeah, don't.

243
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:57,349
Just do it. I'll arrest you if you don't.

244
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,686
We're back to that again?

245
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:04,565
Also, what became of Aoi Sugihara?

246
00:17:05,899 --> 00:17:07,943
I've called her over ten times.

247
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:14,033
SHIKAWAHANACHO

248
00:17:14,116 --> 00:17:16,368
She's at home. Go check on her.

249
00:17:20,831 --> 00:17:25,210
So Kurosaki made Kaga confess
and cooked up that whole plan?

250
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,464
What a crafty bastard.

251
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:30,424
So what should I do?

252
00:17:30,924 --> 00:17:33,761
<i>Pretend to agree</i>
<i>to Kurosaki's offer and buy time.</i>

253
00:17:34,261 --> 00:17:35,137
What?

254
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:39,099
At this rate, the NCD might
get the jump on us again.

255
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:41,894
Yeah, okay, whatever you say.

256
00:17:49,777 --> 00:17:51,320
The report on Noriaki Nagata.

257
00:17:58,285 --> 00:17:59,328
Quick work.

258
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:00,996
Thank you.

259
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:04,124
We ran an inquiry
for Noriaki Nagata in the database

260
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:07,169
and learned that Nagata
is connected to the Saeki Family,

261
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:09,296
which the outlaw Matsubara works for.

262
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:14,218
We believe Nagata purchased cocaine
from the Saeki Family.

263
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:17,137
Nagata.

264
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,810
Never mind small fry like him.

265
00:18:23,393 --> 00:18:27,731
I don't know where the punk is from,
but I doubt he's even alive anymore.

266
00:18:28,232 --> 00:18:29,066
Sir.

267
00:18:30,442 --> 00:18:32,486
Focus on the Saeki Family.

268
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:34,571
To be clear,

269
00:18:34,655 --> 00:18:38,742
I want you to use whatever means it takes
to get them before the NCD.

270
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:08,248
Ow!

271
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,876
Shit.

272
00:20:13,003 --> 00:20:14,213
Stop right there!

273
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:17,925
Are you Aoi Sugihara?

274
00:20:19,259 --> 00:20:21,303
I'm Kurosaki, a narcotics agent.

275
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:31,772
What is this?

276
00:20:35,692 --> 00:20:36,693
It's…

277
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:38,320
Hey, wait!

278
00:20:41,114 --> 00:20:42,658
What are you doing?

279
00:20:42,741 --> 00:20:44,368
Isn't she a victim?

280
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,413
Is that…

281
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:53,710
It can't be.

282
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:56,380
There has to be a mistake.

283
00:20:58,423 --> 00:20:59,549
Answer me.

284
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:01,718
This isn't yours, right?!

285
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:09,434
Let's go.

286
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:10,435
Wait!

287
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:14,314
She wouldn't have done this
if Kaga hadn't drugged her with cocaine!

288
00:21:14,898 --> 00:21:16,483
She's a victim! So why--

289
00:21:16,566 --> 00:21:19,736
She's no longer a victim
if she buys cocaine herself!

290
00:21:20,487 --> 00:21:22,990
We have a responsibility to arrest her.

291
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:25,033
You're a dealer.

292
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:28,245
You should already know
the hell that awaits her.

293
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:30,956
I said, wait!

294
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:40,882
What are you doing?

295
00:21:41,883 --> 00:21:43,260
You can't.

296
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:46,888
Even if it's hard or tough.

297
00:21:47,806 --> 00:21:50,058
You have to endure it.

298
00:21:51,685 --> 00:21:56,565
I said you would hurt those dear to you
and lose everything if you did drugs.

299
00:21:59,359 --> 00:22:00,610
So why?

300
00:22:03,822 --> 00:22:06,241
Please, come to your senses!

301
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:08,869
That man is just preying on you!

302
00:22:08,952 --> 00:22:09,995
No!

303
00:22:10,078 --> 00:22:11,955
We love each other!

304
00:22:12,039 --> 00:22:16,251
He wouldn't make you take drugs
and sell your body if he loved you!

305
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:18,295
This is how they exploit people!

306
00:22:18,378 --> 00:22:21,298
Wrong! You're wrong!

307
00:22:22,507 --> 00:22:24,343
Please, I want a divorce.

308
00:22:25,052 --> 00:22:26,845
Let me be free!

309
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:29,097
You can have Toru.

310
00:22:29,181 --> 00:22:30,223
So please!

311
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:36,813
Please. I'm begging you.

312
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:39,232
Come back to your senses.

313
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:45,447
Please, just come back
to your senses, you idiot!

314
00:23:06,259 --> 00:23:08,720
I'm sorry! Mercy, please!

315
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:10,764
I promise I won't say anything!

316
00:23:10,847 --> 00:23:13,225
I won't tell a soul
that I bought from the Saeki Family!

317
00:23:13,809 --> 00:23:16,394
Please, have mercy on me!

318
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:27,572
<i>How about we go for an eyeball?</i>

319
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:29,366
Don't!

320
00:23:29,449 --> 00:23:32,828
<i>The Saeki Family that has been looking</i>
<i>after us needs some more manpower.</i>

321
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:36,414
<i>One look at how they clean</i>
<i>and I can tell if they're useful.</i>

322
00:23:36,498 --> 00:23:38,750
<i>If they seem trustworthy,</i>
<i>they'll get the goods.</i>

323
00:23:39,251 --> 00:23:42,796
<i>If I infiltrate it, we can grasp</i>
<i>the entire flow of the cocaine.</i>

324
00:23:42,879 --> 00:23:44,005
<i>With this plan,</i>

325
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:48,009
we can get more than just the people
who directly sold the cocaine to Nagata.

326
00:23:48,093 --> 00:23:49,469
The client list.

327
00:23:49,553 --> 00:23:52,597
Search for it. Find it. Bring it to me.
That's the condition.

328
00:23:52,681 --> 00:23:54,182
<i>All right.</i>

329
00:23:54,933 --> 00:24:00,856
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO ACTUAL PERSONS,
GROUPS, OR CASES IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL

330
00:24:00,939 --> 00:24:01,898
Subtitle translation by: Saim Ul Hassan
